# Blueprint Patterns

## Before Writing Code:

1. Check existing blueprints: use MCP recommend_blueprint() or search_blueprints()
2. Review [docs/blueprints/catalog.md](docs/blueprints/catalog.md) decision tree
3. Use extract_pattern() for adding capabilities
4. Reference blueprint files, don't write from scratch

## Module Requirements:

- Official modules preferred (terraform-aws-modules/*, cloudposse/*)
- Version pinning required
- Outputs for resource attributes (enables implicit dependencies)
- Variables with validation and descriptions

## Gold Standard Files:

- Security patterns: [docs/ai-assistant-guidelines.md](docs/ai-assistant-guidelines.md)
- Module structure: blueprints/*/modules/compute/main.tf
- Naming conventions: [skills/style-guide/SKILL.md](skills/style-guide/SKILL.md)
